# Infrastructure Rules (/src/infrastructure/)

> **Compatibility shim:** Cursor uses **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`** as the source of truth. For this layer see:
> - `.cursor/rules/orchestrator-architecture.mdc`
> - `.cursor/rules/orchestrator-layer-infrastructure.mdc` (globs: `src/infrastructure/**`)
>
> This `GEMINI.md` remains for Antigravity / legacy workflows (see **`AGENTS.md` §6**).

## This Is the "Dirty" Layer

Implements contracts from `/core/ports/`. Frameworks and I/O allowed here.

---

## ALLOWED

```
✅ CAN import from /core/ports/ (to implement contracts)
✅ CAN import from /core/entities/ (to work with domain types)
✅ CAN import framework libraries
✅ CAN import database drivers
✅ CAN perform I/O (this is WHERE I/O lives)
```

## FORBIDDEN

```
❌ NEVER import from /presentation/
❌ NEVER import from /core/use_cases/
```

---

## Naming Rules

Names must include BOTH the technology AND the domain concept:

| ✅ Acceptable | ❌ Rejected |
|---------------|-------------|
| `SqliteExpenseGateway` | `Gateway`, `Repository` |
| `InMemoryBudgetGateway` | `Store`, `DAO` |
| `OpenWeatherClient` | `ApiClient`, `Http` |
| `LocalFileConfigSource` | `ConfigLoader` |

---

## Implementation Contract

Every Gateway here MUST:
1. Implement a Port from `/core/ports/`
2. Be stateless or manage its own state (no hidden globals)
3. Be swappable (could replace SQLite with Postgres without touching `/core/`)
